==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trappist
<hw>Trap"pist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>trappiste</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A monk
belonging to a branch of the Cistercian Order, which was established by
<person>Armand de Ranc⟦eacute⟧</person> in 1660 at the monastery of La
Trappe in Normandy. Extreme austerity characterizes their discipline.
They were introduced permanently into the United States in 1848, and
have monasteries in Iowa and Kentucky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1532 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

